{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d5917569-f187-41f3-96ac-3c8cd686337a","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, make these changes in your `.csproj`:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the VSTest opt-in:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it for the project file. `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0` already defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is **not** set to `true`.\n\n3. **Update your test-run command** — replace:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   with:\n   ```\n   dotnet run\n   ```\n   or continue using `dotnet test` (supported from .NET SDK 8.0.400+ / VS 17.12+). If you use an older SDK, you may need to add an `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` property.\n\n4. **Review any VSTest-specific settings** (`.runsettings`, `/p:VSTestLogger`, etc.) — Microsoft.Testing.Platform uses its own CLI args (e.g., `--report-trx` instead of `--logger trx`). Extensions are added via NuGet packages rather than `.runsettings` adapters.\n\n### Quick checklist\n\n| Area | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` | Remove or set to `false` |\n| CI `dotnet test` | Works with SDK ≥ 8.0.400; otherwise switch to `dotnet run` |\n| `.runsettings` | Migrate settings to CLI args / `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| TRX logging | Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package + `--report-trx` |\n| Code coverage | Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` package |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"53098326-b578-42f4-ba42-2fa93b33bb79","outputTokens":448,"requestId":"481E:99ACC:31F42B6:3687C12:69FBE2FA"},"id":"ea4c6dad-7a25-4435-b111-9033219323f0","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:55:32.891Z","parentId":"5d5f34b7-653e-42d5-ab3b-8f64839fb0ae"}
